<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="90" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph blockId="0.[513,1789,617,794]" pageId="0" pageNumber="90">(BAMBOO, TRUE AND RUFFED LEMURS)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="90">• Medium-sized to large prosimians with forelimbs slightly shorter than hindlimbs, elongated, tapering snout, eyes slightly laterally directed, rounded ears (some tuft- ed), short, dense fur, and long tail.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6638670" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6638670" box="[1223,1432,1004,1041]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6638670/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="90" startId="0.[1223,1238,1004,1041]" targetBox="[1495,1848,1027,1216]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1223,1432,1004,1041]" box="[1223,1432,1004,1041]" pageId="0" pageNumber="90">• 60-120 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6638672" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6638672" box="[1224,1444,1206,1239]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6638672/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="90" targetBox="[217,1151,859,1474]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph box="[1224,1444,1206,1239]" pageId="0" pageNumber="90">• Madagascar.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="90">• Dry, subhumid and humid primary and degraded forests, and dense bamboo and vines, reed beds, and papyrus marsh.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1224,1696,1367,1396]" pageId="0" pageNumber="90">% 5 genera, 21 species, 25 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="90">• 4 species Critically Endangered, 4 species Endangered, 9 species Vulnerable; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
